in the world mr dobkin began his career in minsk belarus where after working for several years as a programmer for a large government run enterprise he started his first private software company after immigrating to the united states in  he held technical and leadership positions in prudential insurance colgatepalmolive and sap labs before focusing his fulltime attention on developing epam into the company it is today for the past  years mr dobkin has been increasingly recognized as an instrumental force in opening the vast software talent pool of the former soviet union region and central and eastern europe to the international business community in  mr dobkin has been inducted into the ernst  young world entrepreneur of the year academy and to the elite entrepreneur of the year hall of fame mr dobkin is also a recipient of numerous awards including being named as a csuite standout by forbes in  ernst  young entrepreneur of the years in  for belarus as well as ey’s entrepreneur of the year for  in information technology consulting category in new jersey in  consulting magazine named him to “top  most influential consultants” mr dobkin holds an ms in electrical engineering from the belarusian national technical university show less read more jason peterson chief financial officer jason peterson svp  chief financial officer jason peterson is epams chief financial officer mr peterson brings  years of finance experience to the company from  to  he was employed by cognizant technology solutions and in his most recent role he was vice president of finance ma and due diligence which he held while leading a largescale corporate business process transformation program prior to that he was cfo of the emerging business accelerator and led the corporate financial planning and analysis function before joining cognizant mr peterson was the cfo for ec medical intelligence a venturebacked software and services company and prior to that he served in various accounting and finance roles at ati technologies philips semiconductors and hewlettpackard mr peterson holds an mba from columbia business school and a bachelor’s degree in economics from claremont mckenna college show less read more balazs fejes cohead global business balazs fejes svp  cohead global business mr fejes serves as the cohead of global business with a focus on europe and apac operations in this role he has responsibility for epam’s entire book of business in those regions  mr fejes also continues to oversee the strategy of epams banking and financial services industry business unit helping to drive evolution of key service lines across the unit’s entire global portfolio prior to august  mr fejes served as epams cto and was responsible for ensuring that all of epam systems global offshore and nearshore software development centers were at the leading edge of industry standards for efficiency and quality mr fejes joined epam in  as part of the acquisition of fathom technology a hungarian software engineering firm which he cofounded and where he served as cto prior to cofounding fathom technology mr fejes was a chief software architectline manager with microsoft great plains microsoft business solutions he also served as chief software architect of scala business solutions he is the recipient of numerous awards for programming excellence and has worked extensively in the us and russia show less read more boris shnayder cohead of global business boris shnayder cohead of global business boris shnayder is cohead of global business at epam systems with a primary focus on americas in this role he is responsible for epam’s entire book of business in the region with over  years of experience in it and telecommunications industries mr shnayder brings both industry and global operations leadership prior to his role at epam mr shnayder served as chief delivery officer of globallogic inc senior vice president head of telecom  healthcare and general manager and also served as its vice president of telecommunications  he also held senior software management positions at motorola and telcordia managing teams throughout the us china india and russia mr shnayder received his ms degree in mechanical engineering from the lviv university show less read more elaina shekhter‎ chief marketing officer elaina shekhter‎ chief marketing officer ms shekhter heads up epam’s global marketing and strategy working to integrate a variety of functions that have a material influence on the strategy positioning and global brand of the company she has been with the company in a number of roles including most recently as the global head of business development and prior to that as the global head of the travel and consumer business unit prior to joining epam ms shekhter was with the travel and marketing giant carlson companies in a number of operational and business development roles including head of retail and entertainment for k a spinoff of carlson marketing group prior to carlson ms shekhter was a manager with ernst and young consulting specializing in crm and analytics engagements for notable clients such as m and ge ms shekhter holds an ms degree in information systems and bsba degrees in economic theory and political science from the american university she is active in the software startup and emerging technology community and takes a special interest in sustainability and artificial intelligence initiatives show less read more victor dvorkin cohead global delivery victor dvorkin cohead global delivery mr dvorkin coleads epam’s global delivery organization driving transformation in the company’s delivery solution practices and competency centers prior to his current role he was the head of the north american business unit where he oversaw the operation of epam’s largest business unit with overall responsibility for the quality of services delivered in the north american region mr dvorkin joined epam in  and has been instrumental in driving the companys growth in emerging industries technology and solution practices helping epam to capitalize on the highcaliber eastern european technical talent to deliver better quality productivity and cost efficiencies to epam clients having worked and lived in the unites states and eastern europe mr dvorkin has indepth understanding of global delivery models and brings handson technology experience and working knowledge of multiple industries including travel healthcare insurance and oil  gas mr dvorkin holds a masters degree in applied mathematics from the belarusian national technical university and a phd in information technology from the international it academy in minsk belarus show less read more sergey yezhkov cohead global delivery sergey yezhkov cohead global delivery mr yezhkov coleads epam’s global delivery organization with a focus on building and cultivating the organization’s software engineering skills and extending the delivery knowhow into a broader geographic footprint prior to his position as head of global delivery mr yezhkov led epams independent software vendors  technology industry business unit helping to cement the foundation for epam’s unique product development mindset and approach in this position he focused on strategic clients in the hightech and software product development sectors mr yezhkov has more than  years of technology and management experience including extensive experience with global delivery models he served as cto and as a board member and advisor to several technology companies prior to epam mr yezhkov served as managing director and cto of vested development inc where he was instrumental in driving the growth of vdi from its foundation to the successful acquisition by epam in  mr yezhkov has an ms degree from moscow state university show less read more jason harman cohead global business development jason harman cohead global business development mr harman is cohead global business development at epam systems in his current role he has responsibility for the acquisition of new clients in epam’s target markets and growing epam’s footprint in existing clients he has responsibility for directing epam sales alliances presales and field marketing teams to achieve this aim mr harman joined epam uk operation  years ago and has been instrumental in the growth of the company in europe where he was latter responsible for eu business development and the establishment of several strategic clients mr harman has spent  years in business development roles with the digital services and software engineering space in both europe and the us leading business development and alliances for west coast operations of a digital consulting business and over  years working with central and eastern european technology services companies mr harman is a chemistry graduate of kings college london show less read more yuriy goliyad head of global operations yuriy goliyad head of global operations yuriy goliyad is head of global operations at epam systems in his current role he is responsible for global company infrastructure and shared services mr goliyad brings more than  years of experience in the software development and software services industries to epam prior to his role at epam mr goliyad was cofounder of an it services firm operating in the us and eastern europe which was successfully sold in  he also held multiple executive management roles in product development services companies and has deep knowledge of business operations in central eastern europe asia pacific and north and south america mr goliyad received his masters degree in applied mathematics and computer sciences from the moscow institute of physics and technology show less read more ginger mosier general counsel  corporate secretary ginger mosier svpgeneral counsel  corporate secretary ginger mosier is our senior vice president general counsel and corporate secretary she has served as epam’s general counsel since march  as corporate secretary since january  and as assistant corporate secretary from may  to january  prior to joining epam ms mosier spent approximately eight years in a variety of legal positions with hewlettpackard company in senior counsel and corporate counsel roles advising most recently on global it outsourcing deal pursuits and related services transactions and preceded by advising various hp software divisions and serving as the legal representative for the hp software integration office implementing the acquisition and integration of several software companies before joining hp ms mosier was in private practice at drinker biddle  reath llp with a focus on corporate and technology law after beginning her legal career at baker  daniels ms mosier holds a jd magna cum laude from indiana university school of law at indianapolis where she was a member of the indiana law review and a ba from indiana university purdue university at indianapolis show less read more larry solomon chief people officer larry solomon chief people officer larry solomon is epam’s chief people officer responsible for overseeing all aspects of talent management talent acquisition workforce planning and management as well as other human resource related functions within epam globally  prior to joining epam mr solomon held a number of leadership positions at accenture his most recent responsibilities as senior managing director and north america operating officer included overseeing and managing the full employee lifecycle of all accenture people in the us and canada resource planning recruitment staffing and deployment and performance management prior to that he was the global coo of human resources for nearly three years with overall responsibility for human resources operations he received a bachelors degree in business administration from the state university of new york at albany with a financemis major and spanish language minor he graduated with the magna cum laude distinction in  show less read more media contacts media relations epam sy